Description: Ear-ring consisting of a corroded copper alloy hoop with wire of the same material twisted around it.
Curator's comments: W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80, mentioning "earrings... of wire"
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.82, p.186, pl.28)
